place.name: ANMER
place.gazetteerText: ANMER, a parish in Docking district, Norfolk; near Peddar way, 4 miles E by S of Dersingham r. station, and 11 NE of King's Lynn. Post Town, Dersingham, under Lynn. Acres, 1,420. Real property, £1,290. Pop., 142. Houses, 30. The manor belongs to H. Coldham, Esq.; whose seat is Anmer Park. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £222. Patron, H. Coldham, Esq. The church is small. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
